    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels for Model Risk Level 3. The single shortfall in Test conditions (achievedLevel 2 vs. requiredLevel 3) is considered acceptable because the ASTM F1717 standard defines a single mandatory test configuration and the inter-laboratory reproducibility study provides additional confidence. All quantitative acceptance criteria are satisfied across three independent modeling environments. The overall credibility evidence is judged sufficient to support a Medium assurance level and the model is accepted for the stated COU.",
